Commentary Text: Rajpoot to Russell, out Caught by Unadkat!! And gone! Rajasthan have their man. Russell cannot believe it as he walks back with both his hand along with the bat over his head. KKR in trouble now with half the side back in the dugout. There was a plan and Rajpoot has bowled to it. Third man was up, deep backward point was in place and a deep extra cover. Rajpoot went for the wide yorker and even nailed it, Russell bends down and slices it straight to Unadkat at deep backward point. That was right off the meat but the long boundaries did not help him there. Russell c Unadkat b Rajpoot 24(14) [6s-3]

Commentary Text: K Nagarkoti to Riyan Parag, out Caught by Shubman Gill!! Superbly taken by Gill! This was slashed hard and it went flat to his left but he got across swiftly, tumbling down in time to pouch this inches above the ground. The umpires weren't sure and went upstairs to be doubly correct, although the soft signal was OUT. The third umpire doesn't need many looks to give his confirmation. Another cracking shot that's found the fielder. Was short and wide, Parag back-cut this aerially and had connected well, only to find the fielder. Riyan Parag c Shubman Gill b K Nagarkoti 1(6)

Commentary Text: Cummins to Smith, out Caught by Karthik!! This was only a matter of time, given Smith's fickle approach so far. Backs away for a slog again, this time gets a thin inside edge and it's pouched comfortably by DK behind the sticks down the leg-side. Huge strike, given Smith's form in recent games. The RR skipper looked nervy for some reason from the outset and has to walk back. Just the start KKR were looking for. Smith c Karthik b Cummins 3(7)
